b'Our Pekka Lundmark held his first town hall yesterday. Over 30,000 employees dialed in to hear him answer questions, discuss his priorities and talk about what #TeamNokia means to him. b"With #5G coming on stream, advanced automation in radio network optimization is inevitable \xe2\x80\x93 and #COVID19 has made the need more urgent. 

Network traffic profiles have been turned upside down by the current COVID-19 crisis and associated lockdowns. We have seen increased data traffic from homes, higher voice erlangs and unfortunately, also reduced operator staff for field work. This impacts radio network management and optimization processes in an overwhelming manner, especially at a time when people rely on good network quality and its availability 24x7.

 Read Yatin Dharamshi's blog post on our blog page to learn the role of self-organizing networks."

b'The move to the #cloud is the kind of access network transformation that only happens once every 20 years, which is why operators are unsure how to go about it. 

It\xe2\x80\x99s worth the effort: virtualization and automation in a software-defined access network (SDAN) bring major cost savings and revenue opportunities. 

With 65+ transformation projects under our belts, unique TCO analysis tools, and right-first-time system integration processes, Nokia is uniquely placed to help operators with the transition. Read more in our recent blog post.'

b"Nobody wants to manage a 21st century #broadband network like a 40-year old telephony system. That\xe2\x80\x99s the scale of the transformation facing operators as they begin their move to #SDN and the #cloud. 

How? 

We strongly advocate a use case approach, like @orange with their Access Renewal and Evolution Strategy program. The potential benefits are enormous: automating routine FCAPS tasks alone can save 25-40% of OPEX. We already have more than 250 cloud-ready customers. Are you ready to join them? 

Read Sandy Motley's blog post on our blog page for more."

b'The end of this month marks the 25th anniversary of our CEO Rajeev Suri as a member of the Nokia team. As he reflects on his journey with Nokia, and all of the brilliant people he has been fortunate enough to work with, he is as excited about its future as he is proud of its past. Our technology is already helping farmers grow crops with less water and fewer pesticides, assisting scientists in combating climate change, and keeping the world connected through a global pandemic. 
As important as it is to look back and take inspiration from what has come before, the story of technology never ends. This is only the beginning of a new chapter for Nokia. 
What life-changing innovations can we hope to see over the next 25 years? The only limit is the human imagination. 
#innovation #connectivity #5G'
